[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_2g00v")
reagent_id = "S"
title = "Sulfur"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Symbol:[/cell][cell]S[/cell]
[cell]Element:[/cell][cell]Sulfur[/cell]
[cell]Atomic number:[/cell][cell]16[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]32 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Yellow[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Important properties[/b]
• A non-metal element.
• Burns in oxygen with a blue flame.
• Forms many compounds, especially sulfides and sulfates.
[b]Where sulfur is found[/b]
• In volcanic areas.
• In some minerals.
• In proteins of living organisms.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Production of sulfuric acid (H₂SO₄).
• Used in fertilizers.
• Used in matches, rubber, and chemicals.
[b]Safety[/b]
Burning sulfur produces sulfur dioxide (SO₂), a toxic gas that can irritate the lungs."
